Ms Sturgeon is going head to head against Mr Ross in Holyrood today. Mr Ross has started the session by attacking the SNP's issue of congestion charge on vehicles coming in to Edinburgh, he calls it a tax on anyone who needs to drive. Nicola Sturgeon says there are climate change obligations and a need to reach net zero has to be at the forefront. But Mr Ross hits back and accuses her of not answering question he raised. He says: "She didn't attempt to answer that question." He says everyone wants to do more to meet climate change targets - but in many areas people still need their cars. THIS LIVE BLOG IS CLOSED - READ COVERAGE BELOW...